**3. Tmux Dependency — CI Blocker (lines 15, 71, 113)**
All non-dry-run paths require a live `tmux` server:
- Line 15: `tmux kill-session -t "stampede-$RUN_ID"`
- Line 71: `stampede.sh ... --no-attach` (creates tmux session)
- Line 113: `stampede.sh ... --no-attach --agent-cmd true` (creates tmux session)

Standard CI environments (GitHub Actions) do not provision a tmux server. These paths will fail with `no server running on ...` unless the CI workflow explicitly installs and starts tmux. No implement proper tmux session lifecycle management with detach support.

